linkNewWindow.what: Link opens a new window or tab without prior notice

texts: Readers can always choose to open a link a new window. When a link forces open a new window, it can be confusing and annoying, especially for assistive device users who may wonder why their browser's "back" button is suddenly disabled.

linkDocument.what: Element links to a PDF, Word, PowerPoint, or Google Docs document

texts: This automated checker helps ensure websites contain the features needed for accessible content, things like heading structure and text alternatives for images and audio. It is not able to help you check the documents you link. Most mobile and assistive device users prefer to read text on Web pages, where content reflows to fit the screen. If the document linked here cannot be converted to a Web page, make sure the document is well structured (headings, lists, table headers) and provides alt text for its images.
